Scaffolded from the [pyarnes](https://github.com/Cognitivemesh/pyarnes) Copier template. The code under `src/` is plain Python; pyarnes dev-tool packages (wired into `.claude/hooks/`, `.claude/agent_kit/`, and the `tasks` CLI) augment your AI coding agent during development only.

## Quick start

```bash
uv sync                  # install runtime deps + dev tools (pyarnes-* resolve into the dev group)
uv run tasks help        # list available tasks
uv run tasks check       # lint + typecheck + test
uv run tasks watch       # TDD watch mode
```
{% if adopter_shape != "blank" %}
## Try the example

```bash
uv run scripts/examples/{{ adopter_shape }}/<name>.py   # ls scripts/examples/{{ adopter_shape }}/ to discover
```

These are **PEP 723** scripts: each file's `# /// script ... # ///` header
declares its own deps, which `uv run` resolves into an isolated cached env
— the project venv is not touched.
{% endif %}

## Writing your first test

This project starts with no `tests/` directory. When you're ready to write a test, ask Claude Code:

> "Write a test for my `Greeter` class"

The bundled **python-test skill** (`.claude/skills/python-test/`) scaffolds `tests/unit/` and your first test file for you, following the pyarnes TDD conventions (async-first, Red → Green → Refactor).

## Pulling template updates

When the pyarnes template evolves, you can fold the improvements in with a single task:

```bash
uv run tasks update      # wraps `uvx copier update` behind the scenes
```

Conflicts (if any) are surfaced interactively — review, resolve, commit.

## What's in the box

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) | Dependency management & task execution |
| [Ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) | Linting & formatting |
| [ty](https://github.com/astral-sh/ty) | Type checking |
| [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/) + pytest-bdd + hypothesis | Testing |
| [Bandit](https://bandit.readthedocs.io/) | Security scanning |
| [Radon](https://radon.readthedocs.io/) | Complexity metrics |
| [Vulture](https://github.com/jendrikseipp/vulture) | Dead-code detection |
| [MkDocs Material](https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/) | Documentation site |

Run `uv run tasks help` for the full list of tasks.

